  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6774.67 trading between the max negative gamma strike (6765) and the massive positive gamma wall at 6800, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging stance but approaching heavy selling pressure. The PIN regime with 68.7B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment where dealers will aggressively sell any push toward the 6800 strike (11.2B gamma wall) and provide buying support if we dip back toward 6765. The tight clustering of positive gamma walls between 6775-6800 creates a natural magnet effect that should contain price action within this 35-point range.\n\nKey levels: 6800 resistance (dealer selling), 6765 support (dealer buying), and 6785/6790 as secondary resistance barriers.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy action capped near 6800 with decent support around 6765.",
